End-to-End Cloud Native CI/CD Platform
Built a production-grade CI/CD platform demonstrating modern DevOps practices — automated pipelines, container orchestration, GitOps delivery, and full-stack observability.

Architecture
Code Push → GitHub Actions → Docker Build → Docker Hub
                                                 ↓
                              Argo CD (GitOps) ← K8s Manifests
                                   ↓
                            Kubernetes (Minikube)
                                   ↓
                          NGINX Ingress Controller
                                   ↓
                        Prometheus + Grafana Monitoring


Tech Stack

GitHub Actions · Docker · Kubernetes · Minikube · Helm · Argo CD · NGINX Ingress · Prometheus · Grafana · Alertmanager · Node.js

What I Built

🔹 CI/CD Pipeline — Automated build, test, Docker image push, and manifest update via GitHub Actions

🔹 Kubernetes Deployment — 3-replica deployment with rolling updates, self-healing, liveness/readiness probes, and resource limits

🔹 GitOps with Argo CD — Continuous delivery from Git with automated sync, self-heal, and auto-prune

🔹 Traffic Management — NGINX Ingress Controller for application routing

🔹 Monitoring & Observability — Prometheus metrics collection, Grafana dashboards, and Alertmanager for alerting workflows

🔹 Dockerized Application — Multi-stage Docker builds with non-root user, health checks, and custom Prometheus metrics (`/metrics` endpoint)

Project Structure


├── app/                    # Node.js app + Dockerfile
├── k8s/                    # Kubernetes manifests
├── helm/cloud-native-app/  # Helm chart
├── argocd/                 # Argo CD application
├── monitoring/             # Prometheus + Grafana config
└── .github/workflows/      # GitHub Actions CI/CD


Quick Start

bash
minikube start --cpus=2 --memory=2048
kubectl apply -f k8s/
minikube addons enable ingress
kubectl create namespace argocd
kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml
kubectl apply -f argocd/application.yaml
kubectl create namespace monitoring
helm install prometheus-stack prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack -n monitoring -f monitoring/prometheus-values.yaml


CI/CD Flow


Push to main → Tests run → Docker image built & pushed → K8s manifests updated
→ Argo CD syncs → Rolling update (zero downtime) → Prometheus scrapes new pods

